        </div> <!-- /. row -->
    </div>   <!-- /.box-body -->
</div>  <!-- /.box -->

<div class="row>"
<div class="col-xs-12">
    <div class="box box-info" id="features">
        <div class="box-header with-border">
            <h3 class="box-title">Features</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="box-body">
            <p>
                The Bug Tracker is a Web-based software application for tracking software systems. If your company develops software,
                whether for in-house use or distribution, BugTracker can be used to maintain an accurate record of the software development 
                process on a per-project basis.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>BugTracker helps you track and manage bugs and enhancements in your software development cycle.</li>
                <li>BugTracker can be used on code in development as well as released sofware.</li>
                <li>BugTracker allows for an unlimited number of projects and role-based users.</li>
                <li>User Roles available include Administrator, Project Manager, Developer, and Submitter.</li>
                <li>Access and abilities in projects are based on the user's role.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row>"
<div class="col-xs-12">
    <div class="box box-warning" id="hood">
        <div class="box-header with-border">
            <h3 class="box-title">Under The Hood</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="box-body">
            <p>
                While the look and ease of use of any application is important, what you don't see on the face of the application is critical.
                The technologies utitlized will effect the security and reliability of your tools.  BugTracker utilizes the following methodologies and technologies:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Code-First database schema</li>
                <li>MVC software design pattern</li>
                <li>User and Role Authentication and Authorization through Entity Framework</li>
                <li>Responsive, Bootstrap interface and HTML5</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
    
<div class="row>"
<div class="col-xs-12">
    <div class="box box-success" id="demo">
        <div class="box-header with-border">
            <h3 class="box-title">Live Demo</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="box-body">
            <p><a href="@Url.Action("Login", "Account")">Try out a fully-featured BugTracker</a> as an Administrator, Project Manager, Developer, and Submitter to determine if it is the right tool for you.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>